<h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--mobile-top-margin  " id="details-title">Details</h2>


<div aria-labelledby="details-title">
  
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>The V888/3 application form is for use by companies who issue parking or trespass charge notices. They need to show ‘reasonable cause’ as to why they want information released from <abbr title="Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency">DVLA</abbr> records. This means they will need to explain why they need the information and how they are going to use it.</p>

<div class="call-to-action">
<p>Our guidance <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/giving-people-information-from-our-vehicle-record">‘How we give people information from our vehicle record’ (MIS546)</a> gives further information on how to submit your request.</p>
</div>

</div>
</div>

